column5: Was up north with the family last week and did a ton of fishing including one awesome new back lake (report later), and thought I'd share this cool underwater shot I took. Almost looks like a painting I think.
That is a very nice shot, Mike. Looking forward to your report.
thta Solo is the single most coolest shot i have ever seen in a fishing report....EVER!!! thanks for sharing....uuuh...what camera/setup did ya use?
I just dont get it. Is there a rabitt in there somewhere? But seriously, awesome shot!!
Wow. What is very neat!  Great photo!
Unique under water shot solopaddler  Thanks for sharing Leechman

Olympus Stylus 790 SW, great little camera. Just point and click, plus it's very compact, waterproof, freezeproof and shockproof.  After destroying my first digital I figured I'd best get something idiot proof  .
Awesome underwater shot bud !!!!!...nice fish,and you can even see the rapala too !!!...cheers
dang. for some reason I can't see it...curse you dial-up
Wow...that is a VERY cool pic Mike!
